d's first full campaign in charge, [[Warren Barton]] was purchased for \u00a3300,000 whilst in the league, Wimbledon had another strong season, finishing in 7th place.\n\nNothing came of the plans for a new ground and at the end of the season, Wimbledon's board decided that [[Plough Lane]] was beyond redevelopment to meet the new [[The Football Association|FA]] rule requiring all-seater stadiums.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk/318497.stm|title=A hard lesson to learn|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=1999-04-15|accessdate=2009-06-04}}</ref> Consequently, the club moved to [[Selhurst Park]] before the start of next season, [[groundshare|ground-sharing]] with [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]].\n\n==Final league table==\n{{main|1990\u201391 Football League}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!width=20|Pos\n!width=175|Team\n!width=20|Pld\n!width=20|\n!width=20|W\n!width=20|D\n!width=20|L\n!width=20|F\n!width=20|A\n!width=20|\n!width=20|W\n!width=20|D\n!width=20|L\n!width=20|F\n!width=20|A\n!width=20|\n!width=20|F\n!width=20|A\n!width=30|GD\n!width=20|\n!width=20|Pts\n|-bgcolor=#FFFF00\n|1||align=left| [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] ||38||||15||4||0||51||10||||9||9||1||23||8||||74||18||align=right|+56||||83\n|- style=\"background:#D8BFD8;\"\n|2||align=left| [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] ||38||||14||3||2||42||13||||9||4||6||35||27||||77||40||align=right|+37||||76\n|-\n|3||align=left| [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] ||38||||11||6||2||26||17||||9||3||7||24||24||||50||41||align=right|+9||||69\n|-\n|4||align=left| [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] ||38||||12||2||5||46||23||||7||5||7||19||24||||65||47||align=right|+18||||64\n|-\n|5||align=left| [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] ||38||||12||3||4||35||25||||5||8||6||29||28||||64||53||align=right|+11||||62\n|- style=\"background:#bbccff;\"\n|6||align=left| [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] ||38||||11||4||4||34||17||||5||8||6||24||28||||58||45||align=right|+13||||59\n|-\n|'''7'''