7)|Maidstone United]]\n|\u00a3300,000\n|-\n|20 August 1990\n|DF\n|[[Gary Elkins (footballer)|Gary Elkins]]\n|[[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]]\n|\u00a320,000\n|-\n|21 February 1991\n|FW\n|[[Andy Clarke]]\n|[[Barnet F.C.|Barnet]]\n|\u00a3250,000\n|}\n\n===Out===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Date\n!Pos\n!Name\n!To\n!Fee\n|-\n|3 July 1990\n|MF\n|[[Dennis Wise]]\n|[[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]\n|\u00a31,600,000\n|-\n|15 August 1990\n|DF\n|[[Eric Young (footballer, born 1960)|Eric Young]]\n|[[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]]\n|\u00a3850,000\n|-\n|21 November 1990\n|FW\n|[[John Gayle (footballer)|John Gayle]]\n|[[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]]\n|\u00a3175,000\n|}\n\n:Transfers in: {{loss}} \u00a3570,000\n:Transfers out: {{gain}} \u00a32,625,000\n:Total spending: {{gain}} \u00a32,055,000\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Wimbledon F.C.}}\n{{Wimbledon F.C. seasons}}\n{{1990\u201391 in English football}}\n\n[[Category:Wimbledon F.C. seasons|1990-91]]\n[[Category:1990\u201391 Football League First Division by team|Wimbledon]]\n", "name_user": "Tassedethe", "label": "safe", "comment": "v2.02 - fix links -Andy Clarke", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1990%E2%80%9391_Wimbledon_F.C._season"}
{"title_page": "1995\u201396 Wimbledon F.C. season", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2015}}\n{{Infobox football club season\n|club=[[Wimbledon F.C.|Wimbledon]]\n|season=1995\u201396\n|manager=[[Joe Kinnear]]\n|chairman=[[Sam Hammam]]\n|stadium=[[Selhurst Park]]\n|league=[[FA Premier League|Premiership]]\n|league result=[[1995\u201396 FA Premier League|14th]]\n|cup1=[[FA Cup]]\n|cup1 result=[[1995\u201396 FA Cup#Sixth round proper|Quarter finals]]\n|cup2=[[Football League Cup|League Cup]]\n|cup2 result=[[1995\u201396 Football League Cup#Second round|Second round]]\n|cup3=[[UEFA Intertoto Cup]]\n|cup3 result=[[1995 UEFA Intertoto Cup#Group 10|Group stage]]\n|league topscorer=[[Robbie Earle|Earle]] (11)\n|season topscorer=[[Efan Ekoku|Ekoku]]/[[Dean Holdsworth|Holdsworth]] (16)\n|highest attendance=<span class=\"nowrap\">25,380 vs [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]]</span> <br> <small>(3 Feb 1996, [[Premier League]])</small>\n|lowest attendance=<span class=\"nowrap\">3,717 vs [[Charlton Athletic F.C.|Charlton Athletic]]</span> <br> <small>(19 Sep 1995, [[Football League Cup|League Cup]])</small>\n|average attendance=13,246\n| pattern_la1 = _navyborder\n| pattern_b1  = _Roma1\n| pattern_ra1 = _navyborder\n| pattern_sh1 = _yellow_stripes\n| pattern_so1 = _yellowline\n| leftarm1    = 000080\n| body1       = 000080\n| rightarm1   = 000080\n| shorts1     = 000080\n| socks1      = 000080\n| pattern_la2 = \n| pattern_b2  = _collarred 2\n| pattern_ra2 = \n| pattern_sh2 = _red stripes\n| pattern_so2 = _blackline\n| leftarm2    = E41B17\n| body2       = E41B17\n| rightarm2   = E41B17\n| shorts2     = 000000\n| socks2      = E41B17\n|prevseason=[[1994\u201395 Wimbledon F.C. season|1994\u201395]]\n|nextseason=[[1996\u201397 Wimbledon F.C. season|1996\u201397]]\n}}\nDuring the '''1995\u201396''' English football season, [[Wimbledon F.C.]] competed in the [[FA Premier League]] (known as the FA Carling Premiership for sponsorship reasons). It was their tenth successive season in the top flight of English football and although they finished 14th, lower than on any of the previous nine occasions, they finished high enough to maintain their top flight membership.\n\n==Season summary==\nWith the Premiership's lowest crowds and transfer budget, Wimbledon had begun most of their top division seasons since promotion in 1986 as pre-season relegation favourites, but the \"[[Crazy Gang (football)|Crazy Gang]]\" spirit kept Wimbledon going once again, although their 14th-place finish was their lowest since joining the top flight 10 seasons earlier.\n\n[[Dean Holdsworth]] and [[Efan Ekoku]] were once again a formidable strikerforce, while [[Vinnie Jones]] was as combative as ever and [[Oyvind Leonhardsen]]'s performances attracted attention from several bigger clubs. Manager [[Joe Kinnear]] managed to hold on to all his key assets, as well as adding a few more, over the close season as he grew ever more determined to defy the odds once again. \n\nIt was the last season at Wimbledon for long-serving goalkeeper [[Hans Segers]], who lost his place early in the season to [[Paul Heald]] and was transferred to [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolves]] soon afterwards. Within a few months however, Kinnear had decided on [[Neil Sullivan]] as his regular goalkeeper. \n\nThe season saw Wimbledon play in European competition for the first (and the only) time in their history, in the Intertoto Cup. However, as [[Selhurst Park]] was unavailable the club were forced to play the matches at [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]]'s [[Goldstone Ground]]. The lack of home support affected Wimbledon's performances, and they finished fourth in their group of five after a 4-0 home defeat to [[Turkey|Turkish]] club [[Bursaspor]], a 1-1 draw at [[Slovakia]]n side [[MFK Ko\u0161ice|Ko\u0161ice]], a 0-0 draw with [[Israel]]is [[Beitar Jerusalem F.C.|Beitar Jerusalem]] at home and a 3-0 away defeat at [[Belgium|Belgian]] team [[R. Charleroi S.C.|Charleroi]].\n\n==Kit==\n[[Core (company)|Core]] became Wimbledon's kit manufacturers for the season. [[Birmingham]]-based electronics company [[Elonex]] remained the kit sponsors.<ref>http://www.historicalkits.co.uk/Wimbledon/Wimbledon.htm</ref>\n\n==Final league table==\n{{main|1995\u201396 FA Premier League}}\n{{:1995\u201396 FA Premier League|showteam=WDN}}\n\n;Results summary\n{{Fb_rs|hw=5|hd=6|hl=8|hgf=27|hga=33|aw=5|ad=5|al=9|agf=28|aga=37}}\n{{Fb_rs_footer|s=[http://www.statto.com/football/teams/wimbledon/1995-1996/table Statto]|date=September 2015}}\n\n;Results by round\n{{#invoke:sports rbr table|table|legendpos=b\n|header=Round\n|label1= Ground\n| res1=H/A/A/H/H/A/H/A/H/A/H/A/H/A/A/H/A/H/H/A/A/H/A/H/H/A/H/H/A/H/A/H/A/H/A/A/H/A\n|label2= Result\n| res2=W/W/L/D/W/L/L/L/L/L/L/L/D/L/D/D/D/L/D/W/W/L/L/W/L/L/D/D/D/L/W/W/D/W/W/L/L/D\n|label3= Position\n| res3=4/2/3/6/3/6/9/11/12/14/15/17/16/17/16/17/17/18/18/16/15/15/15/14/16/16/16/15/15/17/15/15/15/15/14/14/14/14\n<!-- -->\n|text_H=Home|text_A=Away\n|color_W=green2|text_W=Win\n|color_D=yellow2|text_D=Draw\n|color_L=red2|text_L=Loss\n|color_1=1st|color_2=2nd|color_3=3rd|color_18-=red1\n\n|source=[http://www.statto.com/football/teams/wimbledon/1995-1996/results Statto.com]\n|date=September 2015\n}}\n\n==Results==\n''Wimbledon's score comes first''<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.statto.com/football/teams/wimbledon/1995-1996/results |title=Archived copy |access-date=22 September 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923060014/http://www.statto.com/football/teams/wimbledon/1995-1996/results |archive-date=23 September 2015 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n===Legend===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|style=\"background-color: #d0ffe3;\"|<small>Win</small>\n|style=\"background-color: #ffffdd;\"|<small>Draw</small>\n|style=\"background-color: #ffd0e3;\"|<small>Loss</small>\n|}\n\n===FA Premier League===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:100%; text-align: